  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-02 07:41 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 3] V6 Cooldown Spec: 600s Gap Filter\n\n**Task:** P3 strategy development \u2014 backtest cooldown thresholds, write V6 spec, finalize deploy plan\n\n**Finding \u2014 600s is the Optimal Cooldown (V3+ hours, n=71):**\n| Cooldown | Kept | Kept WR | Blocked | Blocked WR | Delta |\n|----------|------|---------|---------|------------|-------|\n| 180s (3m) | 68 | 72% | 3 | 67% | +5pp |\n| 300s (5m) | 57 | 70% | 14 | **79%** | -9pp \u26a0\ufe0f |\n| 420s (7m) | 50 | 72% | 21 | 71% | +1pp |\n| **600s (10m)** | **47** | **77%** | **24** | **62%** | **+15pp** \u2705 |\n| 900s (15m) | 41 | 73% | 30 | 70% | +3pp |\n\n- **300s (5m) BLOCKS WINNERS** \u2014 blocked trades have 79% WR! Too aggressive at short intervals.\n- **600s is the sweet spot** \u2014 biggest WR delta (+15pp), blocked trades are genuinely weaker.\n- **900s over-filters** \u2014 starts blocking good trades again (70% blocked WR).\n\n**Finding \u2014 Why 600s Works (Gap Bucket Analysis):**\n| Gap Range | Blocked Trades | WR |\n|-----------|---------------|-----|\n| 0-180s | 3 | 67% |\n| 180-300s | 7 | 71% |\n| **300-420s** | **8** | **50%** \u2190 the problem bucket |\n| 420-600s | 6 | 67% |\n\nThe 300-420s range (5-7 min after last trade) produces coin-flip trades. These are stale signals from the same market move. 600s cooldown catches ALL of these plus the weak 420-600s bucket.\n\n**Finding \u2014 Daily Impact:**\n- High-volume days cut 34-47% of trades (Mar 25: 17\u21929, Apr 1: 14\u219210)\n- Low-volume days barely affected (Mar 31: 1\u21921, Mar 29: 1\u21921)\n- Cooldown self-adjusts: in selective markets, no impact. In noisy markets, maximum filtering.\n\n**Spec Written:** `patches/v6-cooldown-filter.spec.md` \u2705\n- Implementation: 8 lines of code in `run()` method\n- Shadow mode: already partially via v6_cooldown_tag in outcomes\n- Deploy: Apr 13 (after V5a validation week)\n- Rollback: remove cooldown check, restart\n\n**V5a checklist updated:** Added min_price $0.48\u2192$0.50 change to deploy step 3b.\n\n**My thinking:** V6 cooldown is the highest-impact upgrade remaining after V5a. It's mechanically simple (timer), doesn't require new data sources, and has the largest WR improvement in backtest (+15pp). Combined with V5a (min_bias=45), the pipeline becomes: hour filter \u2192 regime filter \u2192 price filter \u2192 bias filter \u2192 cooldown \u2192 conviction \u2192 trade. Each layer cuts the weakest signals.\n\n**Decision:** V6 spec COMPLETE. Deploy Apr 13. V5a + V6 combined estimate: 80-85% WR with 3-4 trades/day \u2192 $35-45 daily.\n\n**Next:** P4 \u2014 alpha research. Pre-session regime check for today's 11h window.\n\n---\n## 2026-04-02 07:11 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] Smart Entry: Price Filter & Evening Loss Autopsy\n\n**Task:** P2 smart entry \u2014 dissect Apr 1 evening failures, analyze entry price filter, find parameter improvements\n\n**Finding \u2014 Morning vs Evening: OBI is THE Differentiator:**\n- Morning wins (n=7): avg OBI=-0.370 (bearish orderbook)\n- Evening losses (n=3): avg OBI=+0.476 (bullish orderbook)\n- Delta: 0.846 OB",
